  <Instrument_Host>
    <name>Mars Atmosphere and Volatile Evolution (MAVEN)</name>
    <type>Spacecraft</type>
    <naif_host_id>-202</naif_host_id>
    <description>The MAVEN mission, launched on November 18, 2013, entered Mars orbit on September 22, 2014, after a ten-month journey. The spacecraft orbits Mars at a 75-degree inclination with a periapsis altitude of 140-170 km, collecting detailed data on the Martian upper atmosphere, ionosphere, and solar interactions throughout a one-Earth-year period. MAVEN will conduct five "deep dip" campaigns, lowering its periapsis to 125 km to study the transition from the lower to upper atmosphere, while sampling various regions of Mars over the course of its mission.</description>
